<div class="header header--code-of-conduct">
  <div class="header__text-box"> 
    <div class="heading-primary">
      <span class="heading-primary--main">code of conduct</span>
      <span class="heading-primary--sub">values and principles we abide by</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="text-container">
  <div class="u-margin-bottom-small">
    <h3 class="heading-tertiary">The following Code of Professional Conduct and Ethics shall be applicable to office bearers and members of all categories of the Society: </h3>
  </div>
  <div class="text-container__list u-margin-top-medium">
    <ul class="text-list">
      <li class="text-list__item">
        Members should at all times preserve the dignity and interest of the profession and of the Society by maintaining a high
        standard of professional and personal conduct;
      </li>
      <li class="text-list__item">
        They should work in the best interest of the Society;
      </li>
      <li class="text-list__item">
        They should neither engage in personal advertisement, nor canvas for an appointment, nor take any action which is detrimental;
      </li>
      <li class="text-list__item">
        They should at all times endeavour to establish and maintain the best possible conditions of service for their colleagues
        and other staff;
      </li>
      <li class="text-list__item">
        When a Member represents the Society, he should as far as possible state the policy of the Society. If he has any disagreement
        with a policy of the Society, he may so inform the Society. The Executive Council will then decide the further course of
        action (including the question of the Societyâ€™s representation) that is to be taken.
      </li>
      <li class="text-list__item">
        Where, having regard to this Code of Conduct a Member wishes to make a complaint against another Member of the Society, he should do so in writing to the Executive Council. If the Executive Council is of the opinion that prima-facie case of infringement of the Code of Conduct has been established it will appoint a Committee for investigation. On the basis of the report of the Committee, the Executive Council will take a final decision on the matter.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="u-margin-top-medium">
    <div class="u-margin-bottom-small">
      <h3 class="heading-tertiary">FOR TEACHERS DEALING WITH STUDENTS: </h3>
    </div>
    <div class="text-container__list u-margin-top-medium">
      <ul class="text-list">
        <li class="text-list__item">
          The teacher must uphold the dignity and honour of his profession. Deal justly and impartially with students despite of their
          multi-cultural backgrounds.
        </li>
        <li class="text-list__item">
          Recognise the differences among students and seek to meet their individual needs. 
        </li>
        <li class="text-list__item">
          Teachers must aid students to develop an understanding and appreciation not only for the opportunities and benefits but
          also for the responsibilities being given.
        </li>
        <li class="text-list__item">
          Inculcate in students respect for teachers, love towards fellow students and loyalty to the institution as well as for the
          country.
        </li>
        <li class="text-list__item">
          Teach them to keep him pure in character and be diligent.
        </li>
        <li class="text-list__item">
          Teachers must conduct themselves with propriety in their profession.
        </li>
        <li class="text-list__item">
          Teachers must conduct themselves with propriety in their profession.
        </li>
        <li class="text-list__item">
          Acquaint students with civic responsibilities and towards the environmental protection.
        </li>
        <li class="text-list__item">
          Accept no remuneration for tutoring except in accordance with the approved policies of Government / Institutions.
        </li>
        <li class="text-list__item">
          Teachers should gain confidence of the students entrusted to their care, rendering to each one for the service and devotion.        
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="u-margin-top-medium">
      <div class="u-margin-bottom-small">
        <h3 class="heading-tertiary">DEALING WITH SOCIETY: </h3>
        <div class="text-container__list u-margin-top-medium">
          <ul class="text-list">
            <li class="text-list__item">
             Must render service to the humanity with full respect.
            </li>
            <li class="text-list__item">
             Adhere to any reasonable pattern of behaviour accepted by the Society.
            </li>
            <li class="text-list__item">
             Respect the community in which you are employed and be loyal to it.
            </li>
            <li class="text-list__item">
             Render possible assistance to the development of the Society and use your knowledge and skill for enhancement of human welfare.
            </li>
            <li class="text-list__item">
             Should be upright, instructed in the art of healing for the good sake of the society.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="u-margin-top-medium">
      <div class="u-margin-bottom-small">
        <h3 class="heading-tertiary">DEALING WITH EMPLOYER: </h3>
      </div>
      <div class="text-container__list u-margin-top-medium">
        <ul class="text-list">
          <li class="text-list__item">
             Employer must actively involve in the functioning and advancement of his/her profession.
          </li>
          <li class="text-list__item">
            He/She should participate in professional meetings as part of Educational programmes, organized by reputed professional
            academic bodies or any other authorized organisations.
          </li>
          <li class="text-list__item">
            Maintain the dignity and interest of the profession by maintaining high standard of professional service and personal conduct.
          </li>
          <li class="text-list__item">
            Co-operate in the development and implementation of institutional policies and programmes.
          </li>
          <li class="text-list__item">
            Conduct professional business through proper adequate channels.
          </li>
          <li class="text-list__item">
            Refrain from discussing confidential and official information with unauthorised people.
          </li>
          <li class="text-list__item">
            Accept no compensation from equipment suppliers and other agencies.
          </li>
          <li class="text-list__item">
            Never engage in any gainful employment outside the institution where the employment affects adversely on the professional
            status or when standing with the students, associates and society.
          </li>
          <li class="text-list__item">
            If any request or enquiry being made by an employer for any good cause, the same shall be duly acknowledged by each and
            very member of the organisation.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="u-margin-top-medium">
      <div class="u-margin-bottom-small">
        <h3 class="heading-tertiary">GENERAL BEHAVIOUR: </h3>
      </div>
      <div class="text-container__list u-margin-top-medium">
        <ul class="text-list">
          <li class="text-list__item">
            One must seek professional growth through study, research, and attending conferences, lectures, professional meetings and
            through other continuing education programmes.
          </li>
          <li class="text-list__item">
            Making the teaching profession ideally so attractive so that other people wants to join in and other practices are to be
            involved in order to attract youth as well.
          </li>
          <li class="text-list__item">
            One must be punctual and regular in their work, corresponding with others and keeping appointments time to time for the
            greater sharing of knowledge.
          </li>
          <li class="text-list__item">
             Encourage one's fellow teachers to adhere to proper ethical behaviour and conduct.
          </li>
          <li class="text-list__item">
            Speak constructively of other teachers and report honestly in matters involving the welfare of students, institution system
            and the profession.
          </li>
          <li class="text-list__item">
            Maintain active membership in professional organisation and through participation, strive to attain the objectives that
            justify such organisations.
          </li>
          <li class="text-list__item">
            Never seek self-enhancement through expressing evaluations or comparisons damaging to other professional workers.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
  </div>
</div>